## hive-exp Experience System

When hive-exp MCP Server is configured:

### When to query (hive_exp_query)
- When encountering build/test/lint errors that aren't obvious typos
- When receiving [hive-exp] hook reminders
- When unsure about a fix strategy

### When to record (hive_exp_record)
- After successfully solving a non-trivial problem with reusable strategy
- Do NOT record: typo fixes, project-specific config, sensitive info

### When to report outcome (hive_exp_outcome)
- After applying a queried strategy, always record the result (success/failed/partial)
- This is the core quality signal — please always report

### Signal naming
- Use canonical signal names from signal-conventions.yaml
- When unsure, check hive_exp_stats(type: "overview") for the signal list
